name: HTMLAnchorElement
description: The HTMLAnchorElement interface represents hyperlink elements and provides special properties and methods (beyond those of the regular HTMLElement object interface that they inherit from) for manipulating the layout and presentation of such elements.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.accessKey
members.description: Is a DOMString representing a single character that switches input focus to the hyperlink.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.charset
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the character encoding of the linked resource.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.coords
members.description: Is a DOMString representing a comma-separated list of coordinates.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.download
members.description: Is a DOMString indicating that the linked resource is intended to be downloaded rather than displayed in the browser. The value represent the proposed name of the file. If the name is not a valid filename of the underlying OS, browser will adapt it.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.hash
members.description: Is a USVString representing the fragment identifier, including the leading hash mark ('#'), if any, in the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.host
members.description: Is a USVString representing the hostname and port (if it's not the default port) in the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.hostname
members.description: Is a USVString representing the hostname in the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.href
members.description: Is a USVString that reflects the href HTML attribute, containing a valid URL of a linked resource.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.hreflang
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the hreflang HTML attribute, indicating the language of the linked resource.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.media
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the media HTML attribute, indicating the intended media for the linked resource.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.name
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the anchor name.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.password
members.description: Is a USVString containing the password specified before the domain name.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.origin
members.description: Returns a USVString containing the origin of the URL, that is its scheme, its domain and its port.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.pathname
members.description: Is a USVString representing the path name component, if any, of the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.port
members.description: Is a USVString representing the port component, if any, of the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.protocol
members.description: Is a USVString representing the protocol component, including trailing colon (':'), of the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.referrerPolicy
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the referrerpolicy HTML attribute indicating which referrer to use.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.rel
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the rel HTML attribute, specifying the relationship of the target object to the linked object.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.relList
members.description: Returns a DOMTokenList that reflects the rel HTML attribute, as a list of tokens.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.rev
members.description: Is a DOMString representing that the rev HTML attribute, specifying the relationship of the link object to the target object.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.search
members.description: Is a USVString representing tThe search element, including leading question mark ('?'), if any, of the referenced URL.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.shape
members.description: Is a DOMString representing the shape of the active area.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.tabindex
members.description: Is a long containing the position of the element in the tabbing navigation order for the current document.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.target
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the target HTML attribute, indicating where to display the linked resource.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.text
members.description: Is a DOMString being a synonym for the Node.textContent property.

members.name: HTMLAnchorElement.type
members.description: Is a DOMString that reflects the type HTML attribute, indicating the MIME type of the linked resource.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.username
members.description: Is a USVString containing the username specified before the domain name.

members.name: HTMLElement.blur()
members.description: Removes theÂ  keyboard focus from the current element.

members.name: HTMLElement.focus()
members.description: Gives the keyboard focus to the current element.

members.name: HTMLHyperlinkElementUtils.toString()
members.description: Returns a USVString containing the whole URL. It is a synonym for URLUtils.href, though it can't be used to modify the value.
